tests/cmp/dc-label-wrong-order.trp:1:27: parse error
  (while parsing DC label)
  1 | let val x = 60 raisedTo `<#root-integrity; #null-confidentiality>`
    |                           ^
  unexpected '#root-integrity'
  expected ';'

Suggestion: Integrity component in wrong position.
  In DC labels, confidentiality comes BEFORE the semicolon,
  and integrity comes AFTER.
  Syntax: `< confidentiality ; integrity >`
  You have an integrity component ('#root-integrity') in the
  confidentiality position. Perhaps you meant to swap them?

